# Player rules document

When you change **gameplay rules** (mechanics, timings, win/lose conditions, powers, phases, play area, elimination, etc.), you **must** update `docs/regles-joueurs.txt` in the same change.

## Source of truth

- `packages/shared/src/rules.ts` — core mechanics
- `packages/shared/src/domain.ts` — phases, player fields, settings
- `packages/shared/src/play-area-layout.ts` — zone sizing, rally/mission geometry
- Client-only timings in `apps/web/static/main.js` only if they differ in production (e.g. dev mode)

## How to update the doc

- Language: **French**, player-facing (no code, no dev jargon).
- Format: short spoken briefing an organizer can read aloud (~1–2 min).
- Cover **all** rules currently in effect: setup, rally, chase, missions, arrest, reveals, powers, boundaries, elimination, victory conditions.
- Keep numbers accurate (seconds, counts, radii described in plain language).
- Do **not** add technical maintenance notes inside the txt file.

If a rules change is reverted or only refactors without behavior change, leave the doc unchanged.
